## String into Arrays

Perhaps the most powerful string method is **`.split()`**.

It takes a string, chops it up at a specific character, and converts it into a full Array [ ]!

```javascript
let csvData = "John,Bob,Alice";

// Split the string wherever there is a comma!
let usersArray = csvData.split(",");

console.log(usersArray); 
// Outputs a real Array: ["John", "Bob", "Alice"]
```

You just turned dumb text into an interactive Iterable Data Structure!
